# Testing Rules

## AAA Pattern (Arrange-Act-Assert)

All tests MUST follow the **Arrange-Act-Assert (AAA)** pattern with clear comments:

```typescript
it('should do something', async () => {
  // ARRANGE: Set up test data and conditions
  const input = { /* test data */ };

  // ACT: Execute the code being tested
  const result = await functionUnderTest(input);

  // ASSERT: Verify the results
  expect(result).toEqual(expectedValue);
});
```

## File Organization

- For each source file `X.ts`, keep **one** and only one test file `X.test.ts`
- Test files live next to the files they test (co-located)
- Use descriptive test names that explain the business requirement
